Chapter 11: The Logic Blade
The purple fire didn't just burn; it screamed. The blast incinerated the mahogany shelves, turning centuries of history into floating embers in a heartbeat.
Ren didn't dodge. He couldn't. The heat was a physical wall, pinning him against the back of the locker.
[Warning: Critical Thermal Exposure.]
[Health: 65/100 and falling.]
[Mana: 10/10]
"You talk about puppets," Kaelen’s voice echoed through the roar of the flames. He hovered a few inches off the ground, the gold circuitry on his suit pulsing in sync with the fire. "But look at you. Still just a boy hiding in a library."
Ren gripped his right wrist. The silver mark was no longer just a pattern; it was carving itself into his skin, glowing with a cold, piercing light that pushed back the purple haze.
[Skill Unlock: 'Logic Blade' Initialized.]
[Cost: 10 Mana (All)]
[Duration: 60 Seconds.]
Do it, Ren thought, his teeth gritted against the pain.
The air in Ren’s hand didn't ignite. It glitched. A jagged, three-foot shard of static—flickering between existence and non-existence—materialized in his grip. It looked like a crack in a mirror, humming with the sound of a thousand deleted files.
Kaelen’s eyes widened. "What is that? That’s not Essence!"
"It’s the truth, Kaelen," Ren said.
Kaelen lunged, his hand a blade of purple plasma. Ren swung the shard of static. When the two forces met, there was no explosion. The 'Logic Blade' passed through Kaelen’s fire as if it weren't there. It didn't cut the flame; it erased the heat.
Kaelen stumbled back, staring at his palm. The fire had been cleanly sliced out of reality, leaving a cold, dead vacuum in its place.
"My power..." Kaelen hissed. "You... you deleted my strike?"
"I’m not cutting you," Ren said, his voice echoing with the same cold clarity as the System. "I’m cutting the permissions the Association gave you."
Ren stepped forward. Every step felt like dragging his soul through broken glass.
[Mana: 4/10]
[Time Remaining: 32 Seconds.]
Kaelen roared, the purple light in his eyes flaring into a blinding supernova. "I am an S-Rank! I am the peak of human evolution!"
He threw a flurry of fire-bolts, each one capable of leveling a city block. Ren moved through the storm, his 'Logic Blade' dancing. Slash. Erase. Slash. Erase. Each bolt vanished into silver pixels the moment it touched the blade.
Ren reached the center of the library. He didn't aim for Kaelen’s heart. He aimed for the gold circuitry on Kaelen’s chest—the "Upgrade" interface.
"Kaelen, wake up!" Ren swung the blade in a vertical arc.
Kaelen tried to catch the blade with his bare hands, confident in his S-Rank shielding. But the 'Logic Blade' ignored shields. It ignored Rank.
CRACK.
The blade struck the center of the gold chest-piece. The purple light turned a frantic, blinding white.
[Critical Hit: System Core Exposed.]
[Action: Forced Disconnect?]
"No!" Kaelen’s voice split—one half was his own, the other was the distorted, synthesized scream of the Administrator. "I... I can't... go back... to being... weak!"
"You were never weak, Kaelen," Ren said, his hand trembling as the blade began to flicker. "You were just being used."
Ren pushed the shard deeper into the circuitry. A massive surge of silver data erupted from the point of contact, throwing both of them in opposite directions.
[Mana: 0/10]
[Skill Deactivated.]
The library went dark. The fires died instantly, leaving only the smell of ozone and ash. Ren hit a fallen shelf, his vision swimming.
Across the room, Kaelen lay still. The purple glow in his eyes was gone. The black combat suit was grey and lifeless, the gold circuits shattered.
[Objective Complete: S-Rank Neutralized.]
[Level Up: 3 -> 5]
[Exp Gained: 2500]
Ren tried to stand, but his legs gave out. In the silence, the sound of heavy boots echoed from the hallway. Not just a few guards—a full battalion.
"Secure the perimeter!" Warden Vane’s voice barked from outside. "The Anomaly has neutralized the Hero! Do not engage from a distance! Use the Null-Field!"
Ren looked at the 'Project Architect' folder lying in the ash nearby. He grabbed it, stuffing it into his jacket. He looked at Kaelen’s unconscious form.
"I'm sorry," Ren whispered.
He looked at the high, shattered windows of the library. He had no Mana. He had no allies. But for the first time, he had the Source Code.
